<h1>Dynatrace Log Shipping — Cost‑Controlled Opt‑In Model for VMs & AKS</h1>

<p><strong>Owner:</strong> Platform Engineering<br/>
<strong>Status:</strong> Active – Sprint implementation (Release end of Sprint 4)</p>

<div class="note">
<strong>Goal:</strong>
<ul>
  <li>Prevent unnecessary Dynatrace log ingestion costs.</li>
  <li>No application logs ingested by default.</li>
  <li>Application owners explicitly opt‑in.</li>
  <li>Clear, documented procedures for VMs and AKS.</li>
</ul>
</div>

<hr/>

<h2>1. Target Concepts</h2>

<h3>Virtual Machines (VMs)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Only minimum platform logs are ingested by default.</li>
  <li>Application logs are ingested <b>only</b> from a defined directory.</li>
</ul>

<h3>Azure Kubernetes Service (AKS)</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Container logs are <b>not ingested by default</b>.</li>
  <li>Application owners opt‑in via namespace labeling.</li>
  <li>Only container <code>stdout / stderr</code> logs are collected.</li>
</ul>

<hr/>

<h2>2. VM Configuration — Dynatrace OneAgent</h2>

<h3>2.1 Define Custom Log Sources (VMs)</h3>

<div class="panel">
<p><strong>Dynatrace UI Path:</strong><br/>
Settings → Log Monitoring → Custom log sources</p>

<ul>
  <li>Rule name: <code>VM-App-Logs</code></li>
  <li>Linux path: <code>/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/*.log</code></li>
  <li>Windows path: <code>C:\Dynatrace\Logs\*.log</code></li>
</ul>
</div>

<img class="screenshot" src="CUSTOM_LOG_SOURCES_VM.PNG"
alt="Dynatrace Custom Log Sources configuration for VMs"/>

<p><i>This ensures OneAgent monitors only those directories for application logs.</i></p>

<hr/>

<h3>2.2 Log Ingest Rule — Default Exclude</h3>

<div class="panel">
<ul>
  <li>Rule name: <code>Exclude-NonPlatform-Logs</code></li>
  <li>Type: <b>Exclude from storage</b></li>
  <li>Paths:
    <ul>
      <li><code>/var/log/**</code></li>
      <li><code>C:\**</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</div>

<img class="screenshot" src="LOG_INGEST_RULE_EXCLUDE.PNG"
alt="Dynatrace log ingest rule excluding non platform logs"/>

<p><i>This rule prevents accidental ingestion of application logs.</i></p>

<hr/>

<h3>2.3 Log Ingest Rule — Allowlist Application Folder</h3>

<div class="panel">
<ul>
  <li>Rule name: <code>Include-VM-App-Log-Dir</code></li>
  <li>Type: <b>Include in storage</b></li>
  <li>Allowed paths:
    <ul>
      <li><code>/var/log/dynatrace/app-logs/*.log</code></li>
      <li><code>C:\Dynatrace\Logs\*.log</code></li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</div>

<img class="screenshot" src="LOG_INGEST_RULE_INCLUDE_VM.PNG"
alt="Dynatrace allowlist ingest rule for VM application logs"/>

<hr/>

<h2>3. AKS Configuration — Namespace Opt‑In</h2>

<h3>3.1 Enable Log Module in DynaKube</h3>

<div class="panel">
<pre><code class="yaml">
spec:
  logMonitoring: {}
</code></pre>
</div>

<p>This enables Dynatrace Log Module to capture container <code>stdout / stderr</code>.</p>

<hr/>

<h3>3.2 Namespace Opt‑In (Application Owner)</h3>

<div class="panel">
<pre><code>
kubectl label namespace payments dt.logs=enabled --overwrite
</code></pre>
</div>

<img class="screenshot" src="K8S_NAMESPACE_LABEL.PNG"
alt="Kubernetes namespace labeling for Dynatrace logs opt-in"/>

<p><i>Only namespaces with this label are eligible for log ingestion.</i></p>

<hr/>

<h3>3.3 Log Ingest Rule — AKS Namespace Allowlist</h3>

<div class="panel">
<ul>
  <li>Rule name: <code>Include-AKS-OptIn-Namespaces</code></li>
  <li>Type: <b>Include in storage</b></li>
  <li>Matcher:
    <ul>
      <li>Kubernetes namespace name IN:
        <code>payments</code>, <code>orders</code>, <code>team-a</code>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </li>
</ul>
</div>

<img class="screenshot" src="LOG_INGEST_RULE_AKS.PNG"
alt="Dynatrace log ingest rule for AKS opt-in namespaces"/>

<hr/>

<h2>4. Verification</h2>

<h3>VM Verification</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Log file in allowlisted directory → visible in Dynatrace Logs.</li>
  <li>Log file elsewhere → not ingested.</li>
</ul>

<h3>AKS Verification</h3>
<ul>
  <li>Namespace without label → no logs.</li>
  <li>Namespace labeled <code>dt.logs=enabled</code> → logs appear.</li>
</ul>

<img class="screenshot" src="DT_LOGS_VIEW.PNG"
alt="Dynatrace Logs view verifying application logs"/>

